    <discussion>Rhynchospora glomerata is often associated with R. capitellata and is
        distinguishable by its taller, slightly stouter habit; longer, slightly paler spikelets; and
        longer and broader fruit body. It is a common lowland weed in the southern Piedmont,
        Atlantic coastal plain, and Gulf coastal plain, where it is often more associated with R.
        inexpansa.</discussion>
